        "<p>led the way, and the whole party swam to the shore.</p>\n<h3>CHAPTER III.</h3>\n<p>A Caucus-Race and a Long Tale</p>\n<p>They were indeed a queer-looking party that assembled on the bankâ€”the</p>\n<p>birds with draggled feathers, the animals with their fur clinging close</p>\n<p>to them, and all dripping wet, cross, and uncomfortable.</p>\n<p>The first question of course was, how to get dry again: they had a</p>\n",
