        "<p>Do you think I can listen all day to such stuff?</p>\n<p>Be off, or Iâ€™ll kick you down stairs!â€</p>\n<p>â€œThat is not said right,â€ said the Caterpillar.</p>\n<p>â€œNot _quite_ right, Iâ€™m afraid,â€ said Alice, timidly; â€œsome of the</p>\n<p>words have got altered.â€</p>\n<p>â€œIt is wrong from beginning to end,â€ said the Caterpillar decidedly,</p>\n<p>and there was silence for some minutes.</p>\n",
        "<p>The Caterpillar was the first to speak.</p>\n<p>â€œWhat size do you want to be?â€ it asked.</p>\n<p>â€œOh, Iâ€™m not particular as to size,â€ Alice hastily replied; â€œonly one</p>\n<p>doesnâ€™t like changing so often, you know.â€</p>\n<p>â€œI _donâ€™t_ know,â€ said the Caterpillar.</p>\n<p>Alice said nothing: she had never been so much contradicted in her life</p>\n<p>before, and she felt that she was losing her temper.</p>\n",
