        "<p>This piece of rudeness was more than Alice could bear: she got up in</p>\n<p>great disgust, and walked off; the Dormouse fell asleep instantly, and</p>\n<p>neither of the others took the least notice of her going, though she</p>\n<p>looked back once or twice, half hoping that they would call after her:</p>\n<p>the last time she saw them, they were trying to put the Dormouse into</p>\n<p>the teapot.</p>\n<p>â€œAt any rate Iâ€™ll never go _there_ again!â€ said Alice as she picked her</p>\n",
