        "<p>Seven flung down his brush, and had just begun â€œWell, of all the unjust</p>\n<p>thingsâ€”â€ when his eye chanced to fall upon Alice, as she stood watching</p>\n<p>them, and he checked himself suddenly: the others looked round also,</p>\n<p>and all of them bowed low.</p>\n<p>â€œWould you tell me,â€ said Alice, a little timidly, â€œwhy you are</p>\n<p>painting those roses?â€</p>\n<p>Five and Seven said nothing, but looked at Two.</p>\n",
