        "<p>Alice did not feel encouraged to ask any more questions about it, so</p>\n<p>she turned to the Mock Turtle, and said â€œWhat else had you to learn?â€</p>\n<p>â€œWell, there was Mystery,â€ the Mock Turtle replied, counting off the</p>\n<p>subjects on his flappers, â€œâ€”Mystery, ancient and modern, with</p>\n<p>Seaography: then Drawlingâ€”the Drawling-master was an old conger-eel,</p>\n<p>that used to come once a week: _he_ taught us Drawling, Stretching, and</p>\n<p>Fainting in Coils.â€</p>\n",
