        "<p>â€œYes, but _I_ grow at a reasonable pace,â€ said the Dormouse: â€œnot in</p>\n<p>that ridiculous fashion.â€ And he got up very sulkily and crossed over</p>\n<p>to the other side of the court.</p>\n<p>All this time the Queen had never left off staring at the Hatter, and,</p>\n<p>just as the Dormouse crossed the court, she said to one of the officers</p>\n<p>of the court, â€œBring me the list of the singers in the last concert!â€</p>\n<p>on which the wretched Hatter trembled so, that he shook both his shoes</p>\n",
