        "<p>â€œAfter that,â€ continued the Hatter, â€œI cut some more bread-and-butterâ€”â€</p>\n<p>â€œBut what did the Dormouse say?â€ one of the jury asked.</p>\n<p>â€œThat I canâ€™t remember,â€ said the Hatter.</p>\n<p>â€œYou _must_ remember,â€ remarked the King, â€œor Iâ€™ll have you executed.â€</p>\n<p>The miserable Hatter dropped his teacup and bread-and-butter, and went</p>\n<p>down on one knee.</p>\n<p>â€œIâ€™m a poor man, your Majesty,â€ he began.</p>\n",
